headline: Targa Resources beats profit estimates on record gas volumes, boosts share buyback program
summary: Pipeline operator Targa Resources beat second-quarter adjusted core profit estimates, driven by record-high volumes of natural gas and natural gas liquids transported through its system. The company also announced a new $1.0 billion share repurchase program in addition to its previous $1 billion plan. Shares were up 2.6% at $167.32 in premarket trading.
